{
  "attrs": {
    "abstract": "This dataset provides a Climate Data Record of Sea Ice Thickness for the northern hemisphere polar region, derived from the RA-2 (Radar Altimeter -2) instrument on the ENVISAT satellite at Level 3C (L3C). This product was generated in the context of the ESA Climate Change Initiative Programme (ESA CCI) by the Sea Ice CCI (Sea_Ice_cci) project.\n\nIt provides monthly gridded sea ice thickness data on a Lambeth Azimuthal Equal Area grid for the period October 2002 to March 2012. Data is only available for the NH winter months, October - April.",
    "catalog_url": "https://catalogue.ceda.ac.uk/uuid/f4c34f4f0f1d4d0da06d771f6972f180",
    "cci_project": "SEAICE",
    "comment": "Northern hemisphere sea ice thickness coverage is limited to the winter month between October and April due to negative effect of surface melt on the retrieval of freeboard. Please consult the Product User Guide (PUG) for more information.",
    "data_type": "SITHICK",
    "ecv": "SEAICE",
    "history": "20180417T093645Z (created)",
    "institute": "Alfred-Wegener-Institut Helmholtz-Zentrum f\u00fcr Polar- und Meeresforschung",
    "platform_id": "Envisat",
    "processing_level": "L3C",
    "product_string": "NH25KMEASE2",
    "product_version": "2-0",
    "project": "Climate Change Initiative - European Space Agency",
    "publication_date": "2018-05-25T11:06:05",
    "references": "Algorithm Theoretical Baseline Document, Sea Ice Climate Change Initiative: Phase 2 (version 2.2)",
    "sensor_id": "RA-2",
    "source": "Altimetry: envisat, Snow depth: Warren Climatology with 50% reduction for first-year sea ice, Mean Sea Surface: DTU15 global mean sea surface, Sea ice Concentration: OSI-SAF Global Sea Ice Concentration (OSI-409), Sea ice type:  ESA-SICCI multiyear ice area fraction from daily gridded NSIDC SSMI-SSMIS brightness temperatures version 4 using the NASA-Team algorithm",
    "title": "ESA Sea Ice Climate Change Initiative (Sea_Ice_cci):  Northern hemisphere sea ice thickness from the Envisat satellite on a monthly grid (L3C), v2.0",
